com.spectratech.controllers

Class PEDDLL

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.spectratech.controllers.PEDDLL

  • public final class PEDDLL
extends java.lang.Object
    The PEDDLL provider contains an Intent action and extras that can be used to start an Activity to do KEYS or PIN related operations.

    • Field Detail

      • ACTION_CLEAR_KEYS

        public static final java.lang.String ACTION_CLEAR_KEYS
        Activity Action: Clear injected keys.

        Clear request injected key or all injected keys.

        This action requests the PEDDLL to clear the specified key/all keys, an implementation should start an activity with or without extra request parameters.

        Activity start without extra parameters will clear all injected keys

        Request parameters

        • EXTRA_KEY_INDEX (optional): The key index of the key to be clear.

        Response result

        • ACTIVITY_RESULT_OK: The request is process sucessfully.
        • ACTIVITY_RESULT_BUSY: The PEDDLL is busy on other process.
        • ACTIVITY_RESULT_PARAM_ERR: Error occurs during extract the request parameters, or invalid parameters.
        • ACTIVITY_RESULT_OPERATION_ERR: The request operation failed.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • ACTION_GET_KEY_STATUS

        public static final java.lang.String ACTION_GET_KEY_STATUS
        Activity Action: Get the key information by key index and key version.

        Retrieve the key information.

        This action requests the PEDDLL to return the current key information, an implementation should start an activity with the request parameters.

        Request parameters

        • EXTRA_KEY_INDEX: The key index.

        Response result

        • ACTIVITY_RESULT_OK: The request is process sucessfully.
        • ACTIVITY_RESULT_BUSY: The PEDDLL is busy on other process.
        • ACTIVITY_RESULT_PARAM_ERR: Error occurs during extract the request parameters, or invalid parameters.
        • ACTIVITY_RESULT_OPERATION_ERR: The request operation failed.
        • ACTIVITY_RESULT_KEY_NOT_INJECTED: The request key is not injected.

        Response Paramters

        • EXTRA_KEY_ALGORITHM: The request key's algorithm.
        • EXTRA_KEY_USAGE: The request keys's usage.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • ACTION_INJECT_KEY

        public static final java.lang.String ACTION_INJECT_KEY
        Activity Action: Perform a key injection.

        Inject a key into the PEDDLL.

        This action requests the PEDDLL save the key for future use, an implementation should start an activity with the request parameters.

        Request parameters

        • EXTRA_TMK_INDEX: The key index of the TMK.
        • EXTRA_KEY_INDEX: The key index of the key to be inject.
        • EXTRA_ENTRYPTED_KEY: The encrypted key content by TMK.
        • EXTRA_KEY_ALGORITHM: The key algorithm of the key to be inject.
        • EXTRA_KEY_USAGE: The key usage of the key to be inject.
        • EXTRA_KVC (optional): The KVC of the key to be inject.

        Response result

        • ACTIVITY_RESULT_OK: The request is process sucessfully.
        • ACTIVITY_RESULT_BUSY: The PEDDLL is busy on other process.
        • ACTIVITY_RESULT_PARAM_ERR: Error occurs during extract the request parameters, or invalid parameters.
        • ACTIVITY_RESULT_OPERATION_ERR: The request operation failed.
        • ACTIVITY_RESULT_KEY_NOT_INJECTED: The request key is not injected.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • ACTION_GET_PINBLOCK

        public static final java.lang.String ACTION_GET_PINBLOCK
        Activity Action: Prompt user to enter PIN.

        Prompt user to enter PIN and return encrypted PIN block if necessary.

        This action requests the PEDDLL to prmopt user to enter PIN, an implementation should start an activity with the request parameters.

        Request parameters

        • EXTRA_KEY_INDEX (not required for OFFLINE PIN): The PIN encryption key index.
        • EXTRA_PAN (not required for OFFLINE PIN): The PAN data exclude checkdigit.
        • EXTRA_KSN (optional): The KSN data.
        • EXTRA_ISN (optional): The ISN data.
        • EXTRA_PINBLOCK_FORMAT (optional): The result PIN block format. Default FMT_ISO9564_1_FMT0.
        • EXTRA_SRED_SUPPORT (optional): SRED support indicator. Default not support.
        • EXTRA_OFFLINE_ONLY (optional): Online/offline PIN indicator. Default Online PIN.

        Response result

        • ACTIVITY_RESULT_OK: The request is process sucessfully.
        • ACTIVITY_RESULT_BUSY: The PEDDLL is busy on other process.
        • ACTIVITY_RESULT_PARAM_ERR: Error occurs during extract the request parameters, or invalid parameters.
        • ACTIVITY_RESULT_OPERATION_ERR: The request operation failed.
        • ACTIVITY_RESULT_INPUT_CANCELLED: The operation is cancelled by user.
        • ACTIVITY_RESULT_INPUT_TIMEOUT: The PIN entry timeout.
        • ACTIVITY_RESULT_PIN_BYPASS: The PIN entry bypass by user.

        Response Paramters

        • EXTRA_ENCRYPTED_PINBLOCK: The encrypted PIN block.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • ACTION_UPI_TMK_INJECT

        public static final java.lang.String ACTION_UPI_TMK_INJECT
        Activity Action: TMK injection process follow UPI.

        Two step TMK injection procedure:

        1. Get encrypted random number from PEDDLL by providing RSA public key.

        2. Send random number encrypted TMK to PEDDLL.

        Step 1 Request parameters

        • EXTRA_UPI_RSA_EXPONENT: The RSA public key exponent.
        • EXTRA_UPI_RSA_MODULUS: The RSA public key modulus.

        Step 1 Response Paramters

        • EXTRA_UPI_ENCRYPTED_RANDOM: The encrypted Random numbers(16 bytes) by RSA public key.
        • EXTRA_UPI_RVC: Check value for Random number.

        Step 2 Request parameters

        • EXTRA_UPI_TMK_INDEX: Key index for inject TMK.
        • EXTRA_UPI_ENCRYPTED_KEY: Random key encrypted TMK.
        • EXTRA_UPI_KVC: Check value for TMK.

        Response result

        • ACTIVITY_RESULT_OK: The request is process sucessfully.
        • ACTIVITY_RESULT_BUSY: The PEDDLL is busy on other process.
        • ACTIVITY_RESULT_PARAM_ERR: Error occurs during extract the request parameters, or invalid parameters.
        • ACTIVITY_RESULT_OPERATION_ERR: The request operation failed.
        • ACTIVITY_RESULT_INVALID_KVC: KVC not match.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
